com.i2group.apollo.alertfeedretrievalservice.transport

Class AlertFeedInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.i2group.apollo.alertfeedretrievalservice.transport.AlertFeedInfo

  • public final class AlertFeedInfo
extends Object
    Information that describes an alert feed to a client, including the ItemIdentifier of the feed, the ItemIdentifier of the Item (or ItemPlaceholder) being monitored, and an indication of how the current user receives alerts from the feed.
    Since:
    3.0

      Constructs a new AlertFeedInfo, initializing all mandatory fields.

    • Constructor Detail

      • AlertFeedInfo

        public AlertFeedInfo(ItemIdentifier alertFeedIdentifier,
                     ItemIdentifier alertSubjectIdentifier)
        Constructs a new AlertFeedInfo, initializing all mandatory fields.
        Parameters:
        alertFeedIdentifier - The ItemIdentifier of the alert feed.
        alertSubjectIdentifier - The ItemIdentifier of the Item or ItemPlaceholder that is the subject of the alert feed. (That is, the Item being monitored, or the set containing the Items being monitored.)

    • Method Detail

      • getAlertFeedIdentifier

        public ItemIdentifier getAlertFeedIdentifier()
        Gets the ItemIdentifier of the alert feed described by this AlertFeedInfo.
        Returns:
        See above.

      • getAlertSubjectIdentifier

        public ItemIdentifier getAlertSubjectIdentifier()
        Gets the ItemIdentifier of the Item or ItemPlaceholder that is the subject of the alert feed described by this AlertFeedInfo.

        An ItemPlaceholder can be the subject of an alert feed if the original subject Item has acted as the source in a merge operation.

        Returns:
        See above.

      • getAlertDeliveryMechanisms

        public List<AlertDeliveryMechanism> getAlertDeliveryMechanisms()
        Gets the AlertDeliveryMechanisms by which the current user is subscribed to the alert feed described by this AlertFeedInfo.
        Returns:
        See above, or null (or an empty list) if the current user is not subscribed.

      • getAlertFeedSubscriptionToken

        public String getAlertFeedSubscriptionToken()
        Gets a String that characterizes the subscription relationship between the current user and the alert feed.
        Returns:
        See above, or null if the current user is not subscribed.
